{"title_page": "Banana Sundae", "text_new": "{{Distinguish|The Banana Splits}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Banana Sundae\n| show_name_2              = Banana Split <small>(2008\u20132011)</small> <br> Banana Split: Daily Servings <small>(2009\u20132011)</small> <br> Banana Split: Lafternoon Delight <small>(2011)</small> <br> Banana Nite <small>(2013\u20132015)</small> <br> Banana Split Extra Scoop <small>(2011\u20132015)</small> <br> Banana Sundae <small>(2015\u2013present)</small>\n| image                    = Bananasundaetitlecard.jpg\n| genre                    = [[Sketch comedy|Gag show]] <br> [[Stand-up comedy]]\n| creator                  = [[Edgar Mortiz]]\n| developer                = [[ABS-CBN|ABS-CBN Corporation]]\n| director                 = Edgar Mortiz <br> Jose Mari Reyes\n| executive_producer       = Rocky Ubana\n| location                 = Studio 2, [[ABS-CBN Broadcasting Center]], [[Diliman]], [[Quezon City]]\n| presenter                = [[#Cast|See cast]]\n| country                  = [[Philippines]]\n| language                 = [[Filipino language|Filipino]]\n| runtime                  = 60 minutes\n| company                  = [[Star Cinema|Star Creatives TV]]\n| network                  = [[ABS-CBN (TV network)|ABS-CBN]]\n| picture_format           = [[480i]] ([[standard-definition television|SDTV]]) <br> [[1080i]] ([[high-definition television|HDTV]])\n| first_aired              = {{start date|2008|10|11}}\n| last_aired               = present\n| preceded_by              = ''[[That's My Doc]]''\n| website                  = http://bananasundae.abs-cbn.com/\n}}\n\n'''''Banana Sundae''''' (formerly '''''Banana Split''''') is a [[Philippines|Philippine]] [[comedy]] [[Sketch comedy|gag show]] broadcast by [[ABS-CBN (TV network)|ABS-CBN]]. The show premiered on October 11, 2008, and currently airs every Sunday from 2:30 PM to 3:30 PM, on the network's ''Yes Weekend!'' block. It also airs worldwide via [[The Filipino Channel|TFC]].\n\n==History==\n'''''Banana Split''''' is a spiritual successor to the comedy program ''[[Goin' Bananas (TV series)|Goin' Bananas]]'' that featured [[Edgar Mortiz]], [[Christopher de Leon]], [[Jay Ilagan]], and [[Johnny Delgado]].\n\n''Banana Split'' debuted on October 11, 2008 with an all-girl cast led by [[Angelica Panganiban]] and [[Cristine Reyes]], with different male celebrity guests each week. The second season premiered on February 28, 2009, and the third season on April 18, 2009 with a new cast, including [[John Prats]], [[Zanjoe Marudo]], [[Jayson Gainza]], [[Pooh (comedian)|Pooh]], and [[Pokwang]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.abs-cbn.com/Feature/Article/3058/Pokwang-on-joining-Banana-Split-Hindi-ko-naman-po-sinulot-ibinigay-sa-akin-ng-kusa-.aspx | title = Pokwang on joining Banana Split: \u2018Hindi ko naman po sinulot, ibinigay sa akin ng kusa\u2019 | publisher = ABS-CBN | date = 2009-03-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title = Banana Split includes new stars for third season | url = https://www.pep.ph/guide/tv/3701/banana-split-includes-new-stars-for-third-season | publisher = PEP | date = 2009-04-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.abs-cbn.com/Feature/Article/3068/Are-John-Prats-Jayson-Gainza-and-Zanjoe-Marudo-the-new-Bad-Bananas-.aspx | title=Are John Prats, Jayson Gainza, and Zanjoe Marudo the new \u2018Bad Bananas?\u2019 | publisher = ABS-CBN | date = 2009-04-14}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.abs-cbn.com/Feature/Article/3066/Has-Pooh-changed-for-the-worse-because-of-his-success-in-showbiz-.aspx | title = Has Pooh changed for the worse because of his success in showbiz? | publisher = ABS-CBN | date=2009-04-14}}</ref><ref>[http://www.pep.ph/guide/3732/Banana-Split-will-introduce-new-segments-starting-April-18 Banana Split will introduce new segments starting April 18] retrieved via http://www.pep.ph 04-18-2009</ref> The fourth season premiered on July 18, 2009.<ref>[http://www.pep.ph/guide/4322/Banana-Split-marks-its-fourth-season-on-ABS-CBN Banana Split marks its fourth season on ABS-CBN] http://www.pep.ph July 22, 2009</ref> On September 30, 2009, a 30-minute weekday afternoon edition called '''''Banana Split: Daily Servings''''' originally aired every Mondays to Fridays on the network's ''Hapontastic'' afternoon block.<ref>[http://www.abs-cbn.com/TV/Article/5012/Default.aspx Jaysona Boto SAlSAL gears up for the new season of Banana Split] retrieved via http://www.abs-cbn.com 09-24-2009</ref> The timeslot later moved to ''Umaganda'' weekday morning block from 10:00{{nbsp}}AM to 10:30{{nbsp}}AM starting August 2010, but was moved again twice as early from 9:00{{nbsp}}AM to 9:30{{nbsp}}AM on June 27, 2011. On July 9, 2011, the original Saturday edition was reformatted as '''''Banana Split: Extra Scoop''''', featuring live comedy performances and also includes the second season of ''Clown in a Million'' segment, a reality comedy search. On September 12, 2011, ''Banana Split: Daily Servings'' was renamed to '''''Banana Split: Lafternoon Delight''''' as the timeslot moved to 2:45{{nbsp}}PM as part of ''Kapamilya Gold'' afternoon block. However, it was later cancelled on October 7, 2011.\n\n''Banana Split: Extra Scoop'' garnered high ratings on its Saturday late-night timeslot compare to the counterpart programs. Due to the success, ABS-CBN launched a late-weeknight edition called '''''Banana Nite''''' which premiered on February 25, 2013 every Mondays to Fridays right after ''[[Bandila (TV program)|Bandila]]''. ''Banana Nite'' extended its airtime to 45 minutes on August 5, 2013, but was later reverted to 30 minutes on February 10, 2014 onwards. ''Banana Nite'' ended on October 30, 2015 after a two-year run. Meanwhile, ''Banana Split: Extra Scoop'' ended on November 7, 2015 after its four-year run. The show reformatted on November 15, 2015 as '''''Banana Sundae''''' which now airs every Sunday afternoons at 2:30{{nbsp}}PM right after ''[[ASAP (TV program)|ASAP Natin 'To]]''.\n[[File:bsplit-logo.png|250px|thumb|right|''Banana Split'' original logo <small>(2008\u20132015)</small>]]\n\nOn April 2020, Banana Sundae was temporarily put off the air, in response to rival network GMA extending ''Kapuso Movie Festival'' to a two-movie block, which made the network extend the Sunday edition of ''KB Family Weekend'' to two movies, causing [[ASAP (TV program)|ASAP Natin 'To]] shorten to a 1-hour airtime in Banana Sundae's timeslot, as part of ABS-CBN's temporary programming changes due to the [[2020 Luzon enhanced community quarantine|2020 Luzon lockdown]], which is part of the [[COVID-19 pandemic in the Philippines|COVID-19 pandemic in the country]]. These changes are expected to last until the end of the Luzon Lockdown on May 2020.\n\n==Cast==\n;Current cast\n*[[Angelica Panganiban]] <small>(2008\u2013present)</small>\n*[[John Prats]] <small>(2009\u2013present)</small>\n*[[Jayson Gainza]] <small>(2009\u2013present)</small>\n*[[Pooh (comedian)|Pooh]] <small>(2009\u2013present)</small>\n*Badjie Mortiz <small>(2009\u2013present)</small>\n*[[Pokwang]] <small>(2009\u20132011; 2015\u2013present)</small>\n*[[Ryan Bang]] <small>(2010\u2013present)</small>\n*Jobert Austria <small>(2011\u2013present)</small>\n*[[SexBomb Girls#Former Members|Sunshine Garcia]] <small>(2011\u2013present)</small>\n*[[JC de Vera]] <small>(2013\u2013present)</small>\n*[[Aiko Climaco]] <small>(2013\u2013present)</small>\n*[[Ritz Azul]] <small>(2017\u2013present)</small>\n*[[Wacky Kiray]] <small>(2017\u2013present)</small>\n* [[Barbie Imperial]] <small>(2020)</small>\n\n;Former cast\n*[[Cristine Reyes]] <small>(2008\u20132009; 2010)</small>\n*[[Roxanne Guinoo]] <small>(2008\u20132009)</small>\n*[[Valerie Concepcion]] <small>(2008\u20132009)</small>\n*[[Dianne Medina]] <small>(2008\u20132009)</small>\n*[[Princess Ryan]] <small>(2008\u20132010)</small>\n*[[RR Enriquez]] <small>(2008\u20132011)</small>\n*[[Zanjoe Marudo]] <small>(2009\u20132010; 2013\u20132015)</small>\n*[[Ni\u00f1a Jose]] <small>(2009\u20132011)</small>\n*A.A. Ponce <small>(2009\u20132011)</small>\n*[[Melai Cantiveros]] <small>(2010\u20132015)</small>\n*[[Gabriel Valenciano|Gab Valenciano]] <small>(2010\u20132011)</small>\n*[[Jason Francisco]] <small>(2010\u20132012)</small>\n*[[Jef Gaitan]] <small>(2010\u20132015)</small>\n*Le Chazz <small>(2010\u20132015)</small>\n*Alora Sasam <small>(2012\u20132015)</small>\n*[[Boom Labrusca]] <small>(2012\u20132015)</small>\n*[[Manuel Chua]] <small>(2013\u20132015)</small>\n*[[Alex Gonzaga]] <small>(2013\u20132015)</small>\n*[[Kean Cipriano]] <small>(2013\u20132015)</small>\n*[[Jennica Garcia]] <small>(2014)</small>\n*[[Mitoy Yonting]] <small>(2014\u20132015)</small>\n*[[Jessy Mendiola]] <small>(2015\u20132017)</small>\n*[[Shine Kuk]] <small> (2017\u20132018)</small>\n\n==Portions==\n\n===Current portions/segments===\n* Aquiknow and Aboonduh Tonite - A parody of defunct late-night talk show ''[[Aquino & Abunda Tonight]]'' hosted by [[Kris Aquino]] and [[Boy Abunda]]. This portion is played by [[Angelica Panganiban]] as Krissy Aquiknow, and [[Jayson Gainza]] as Bhoy Aboonduh.\n* Krissy TV - A parody of defunct morning talk show ''[[Kris TV]]'' hosted by [[Kris Aquino]]. It is portrayed by [[Angelica Panganiban]] as Krissy Aquiknow, [[Jayson Gainza]] as Krissy's assistant Dharla (a parody of ''Kris TV'' headwriter Darla Sauler), and [[John Prats]] as [[Bimby Aquino Yap]].\n* Clown in a Million - The talent search for comedians, where funny people with no or little television experience battle it out to be proclaimed as the latest comedic talent discovery.\n* Banana Classics - A sketch or comic skit where two or more actors portray roles to convey a simple story that culminates in a punchline, just to make people laugh. It is done before a live audience without cuts, thus requiring the material to be visual rather than verbal.\n* Extra Spoof - A segment where the cast impersonates famous icons, idols and celebrities of past and present times, living or deceased. It is cohesively presented with a common theme like novelty icons, the icons from the 80s, 90s and 2000s, or internationally known Pinoy singers.\n* Make Me Rap - \n* Oh My Shopping! - A parody of [[O Shopping]] where the cast is asked to pick a certain item from a chosen box which they need to sell like an infomercial show.\n\n;Former segments (from ''Banana Nite'' and ''Banana Sundae'')\n* Barado Sisters (later as \"Hala Bara!\")\n* Eto na Post\n* Kandila (parody of late-night newscast ''[[Bandila (TV program)|Bandila]]'')\n** Ihaw Na! (parody of ''Ikaw Na!'', a defunct Bandila segment)\n* Krissy and Me (parody of ''[[Kris TV]]'')\n* Laugh Three\n* \"Painting\"\n* Surprise Bwi-set\n* Tres Kumpares\n* Rated SSPG: Sobra-sobrang Pilyong Gags, Bawal Sa Bata, Tulog Na! (a parody of [[Movie and Television Review and Classification Board|MTRCB]]'s SPG rating advisory, a collection of [[Off-color humor|green jokes]])\n* Chazz Do It\n* Yaya and Angel (parody of ''Ang Spoiled'', a sketch from rival gag show ''[[Bubble Gang]]'')\n* Mr. Bang (parody of ''[[Mr. Bean]]'')\n* Aquiknow & Aboonduh Tonite (parody of ''[[Aquino & Abunda Tonight]]'')\n* Sosyal, 'Di Sosyal\n* Banana Recap\n** Monday Funday\n** Timeless Tuesday\n** Wayback Wednesday\n** Throwback Thursday\n** Flashback Friday\n* Maling Akala\n* Dr. Selfie\n* Balitang Six-Six\n* Fake Yan\n* Pag May Time\n* Kontra Pick-Up\n* ''[[Pinoy True Stories]]'' parodies\n** TnT: Tapatan ni Tunting (parody of ''[[Pinoy True Stories|Tapatan ni Tunying]]'')\n** Bistodo (parody of ''[[Pinoy True Stories|Bistado]]'')\n** Kutya ng Masa (parody of ''[[Pinoy True Stories|Mutya ng Masa]]'')\n* How Dare You (parody of reality show ''[[I Dare You (Philippine TV series)|I Dare You]]'')\n* Single, In a Relationship, It's Complicated\n* Munting Kaalaman\n* Pogi vs. Tambay\n* Hot Issue\n* Brad Bro Bru\n* Isang Tanong, Isang Sagot\n\n===Former portions/segments===\n{| class=\"wikitable collapsible collapsed\" style=\"width: 99%\"\n! colspan