in a practical joke segment following a dating game format, where they kissed an extra gay instead of the ''Banana Split'' girls. This event caused a short rift between Rafael and a ''Banana Split'' executive producer. As a result, few clips were aired instead of the whole segment. A public apology was also delivered after the end of the show.<ref>{{cite web| title= \"Banana Split\" EP surprised by Rafael Rosell's interview about attempted gay-kissing \"playtime\" | url= http://www.pep.ph/news/19984/Banana-Split-EP-surprised-by-Rafael-Rosells-interview-about-attempted-gay-kissing-playtime/2 | author = Roldan Castro | publisher= PEP | date = 2008-11-21}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title = Rafael Rosell upset by bad joke in 'Banana Split' | url=http://www.pep.ph/news/19979/Rafael-Rosell-upset-by-attempted-kiss-on-the-lips-by-gays-in-Banana-Split | author = Archie de Calma | publisher = PEP | date = 2008-11-21}}</ref><ref>[http://www.abs-cbn.com/Feature/Article/1822/Why-Rafael-Rosell-did-not-find-The-Banana-Split-practical-joke-funny-.aspx Why Rafael Rosell did not find The Banana Split practical joke funny] Retrieved via http://www.abs-cbn.com 11-29-2008</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.pep.ph/news/19984/Banana-Split-EP-surprised-by-Rafael-Rosell | title = \"Banana Split\" EP surprised by Rafael Rosell's interview about attempted gay-kissing \"playtime\" | publisher = PEP | date=2008-11-21}}</ref>\n\n===Casting cut-out===\n{{Confusing|section|date=June 2011}}\nValerie Concepcion, Roxanne Guinoo and Dianne Medina left ''Banana Split'' to focus on ''Precious Hearts Romances'' series where they will act in different episodes. It was reported that Guinoo removed from the show because of her weight problems,<ref>{{cite web | title = Was Roxanne Guinoo removed from \u2018Banana Split\u2019 due to weight problems? | url=http://www.abs-cbn.com/Feature/Article/3031/Is-Roxanne-Guinoo-axed-from-Banana-Split-due-to-her-increasing-weight-.aspx | publisher = ABS-CBN | author = Rachelle Siazon | date = 2009-04-03}}</ref> while Concepcion left the show due to a talent fee dispute.<ref>{{cite web | title=Valerie Concepcion is leaving Banana Split because of a talent fee dispute | url=http://www.abs-cbn.com/Feature/Article/3029/-Valerie-Concepcion-is-leaving-Banana-Split-because-of-a-talent-fee-dispute.aspx | author = Napoleon Quintos | publisher = ABS-CBN | date = 2009-04-03 }}</ref> The rift between Angelica Panganiban and Cristine Reyes arose as another issue, resulting in Reyes' departure.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.abs-cbn.com/Feature/Article/3030/Cristine-Reyes-Walang-away-sa-Banana-Split-.aspx | title = Cristine Reyes: \u2018Walang away sa Banana Split.\u2019 | publisher = ABS-CBN | date = 2009-04-03 | author = Napoleon Quintos}} [[TVTropolis]]</ref>\n\n===Binay Blackface skit===\n''Banana Sundae'' attracted controversy prior to the May 13, 2019 elections when they aired a skit parodying the church argument of Binay siblings [[Abigail Binay|Abby Binay]] and [[Jejomar Binay Jr.|Junjun Binay]], who were both Makati mayoral candidates. Pooh and former SexBomb Girls member Sunshine Garcia played as the Binay siblings, putting black makeup on themselves. The skit drew mixed reactions with viewers calling it \"racist and insensitive\" as well as referencing the history of [[blackface]], while others noted that the show never mocked skin color, but instead, the argument itself and the political history of the Binay family.\n\n==SPG rating==\n''Banana Sundae'' is given an SPG rating by the [[Movie and Television Review and Classification Board|Movie and Television Review and Classification Board (MTRCB)]] due to themes and strong languages not suitable for very young audiences.\n\n==Accolades==\n* 24th PMPC Star Awards for Television's \"Best Gag Show\" \u2013 ''Banana Split'' (Won)\n* 24th PMPC Star Awards for Television's \"Best Comedy Actress\" \u2013 Angelica Panganiban (Won)\n* 23rd PMPC Star Awards for Television's \"Best Gag Show\" 